{"key":"post-7223863","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>7223863</id>\n<content>Sometimes, especially with wood or straw substrates, you can cover the entire spot with a salt paste to kill the mold.  Remember, the green is the spores.  If you disturb them, they go airborne and spread everywhere. Cover an area about 1/2&quot;/1cm away from the edges of the green with your salt paste.  Use about a tablespoon of salt and a few drops of water. Make it the consistency of honey.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>7223978</next>\n<prev>7223480</prev>\n<first>7190557</first>\n<last>27730552</last>\n<when>1185417100</when>\n<utime>07/26/07 05:31 AM</utime>\n</post>"}